\f1\fs24 \'93I have no special talents, I am only passionately curious\'94 \'97 Albert Einstein\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 \'93Curiosity is insubordination in its purest form\'94 \'97 Vladimir Nabokov\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 The more he learned, the more he wanted to learn\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 Humans possess a fourth drive, pure curiosity\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 Curiosity is unruly, it doesn\'92t like rules, it finds most of them are actually provisional\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 \cf2 People who defer too much to the authority of their authority of elders\'92 ideas are less likely to transcend them\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 the truly curios will be increasing demand\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 the curious are most likely to make creative connections between different fields, of the kind that lead to new ideas and the ones best suited to working in multidisciplinary teams\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 our curiosity is highly responsive to the situation or environment we are in\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 diversive curiosity manifests itself as a restless desire for the new and the next\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 unfettered curiosity is wonderful, un-channeled curiosity is not\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 epistemic curiosity is deeper, more disciplined and effortful than diversive curiosity\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 empathetic curiosity makes you wonder \'93why they did it\'94\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
